<DESCRIPT>  PAST; BASEBALL; PROFESSIONAL; CINCINNATI; MOVIE; CONTROVERSY  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  The producers of a made-for-TV movie titled "The Babe Ruth Story" may have to
rewrite one scene in which Pete Rose is supposed to portray Ty Cobb in a
Detroit Tigers uniform.;    At first, spokesman Rich Levin said baseball
wouldn't try to keep Rose from making a living. Later, he said more
information was needed.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  IS ROSE IN UNIFORM A NO-NO?  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  Baseball Notes  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     "After doing some checking, there may be some problem with Pete Rose
wearing a licensed Major League Baseball uniform," Levin said.;    "This is
the first I've heard of it. It's something the commissioner has to be alerted
to, and also our lawyers.";    NBC said Rose would appear in the movie as the
Tigers' player-manager in the 1920s, meeting Ruth in a hotel and in a Tigers
uniform on a baseball diamond.;  TEMPLETON FOR TEUFEL: The New York Mets
traded infielder Tim Teufel to the San Diego Padres for shortstop Garry
Templeton. Mets General Manager Frank Cashen said Templeton will back up Kevin
Elster.;  ETC.: Major league baseball players will not be allowed to play in
the Olympics for many years, officials said during a conference on the
international areas of the sport. . . . Cincinnati Reds third baseman Chris
Sabo is suing his former agent for $8.75 million, alleging that Frederick
Sofen did not file the player's 1989 income tax return, misused fan club money
and spent a $20,000 check written by Sabo to cover tax liabilities.  </TEXT>
